<font color="#FF0000">MORE ON WAR &amp; VIOLENCE</font><br>
<tt>Thu Mar 13 12:07:54 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Lucien,<br>
Your thoughts on war itself being something other than violence I find interesting.  I suppose the fact that we had a 45 year Cold War influenced the way you think about war.  Whether or not all the swords finally get turned into plowshares depends on two things: 1. The foregoing of any attempt to obtain a goal through force or other type of pressure. 2.  The day when we all can deal constructively with the anger in own hearts without exploding into violence.  <br>
Gerry<br>
